BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:SPRING BY THE RIVER MARKET
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260321T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260321T210000
UID:762eab9108a2df288e34a85165d74817@petalumariverpark.org
DESCRIPTION:Come stroll\, shop\, savor\, and soak up the energy of the sea
 son at the debut of Spring by the River Market—our first ever intergener
 ational community marketplace celebrating the Spring Equinox! From sweet t
 reats to artisanal coffee and juices\, painted alebrijes to hand-crafted a
 rtworks and jewelry\, custom bouquets to self-care products\, plus face-pa
 inting\, family portraits\, multi-cultural performances\, and much more! T
 his is just a taste of what Petaluma River Park Foundation and our Communi
 ty Park Designers have in store! Come see how together\, we're transformin
 g the park into a vibrant community experience for all! .fe-block-235ed299
 2b5eca79a65a {mix-blend-mode: \; } LET US KNOW YOU'RE JOINING US! #block-y
 ui_3_17_2_1_1772567475472_7568 {--sqs-block-content-flex: 0\; } SCHEDULE O
 F ACTIVITIES 10:00 a.m. - 11:00 a.m. Opening Ceremony hosted by Coast Miwo
 k tribal citizens of Federated Indians of Graton Rancheria and Danza Aztec
 a Calpulli XochilYauhtli 10:00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m. FREE Face Painting by Keyy
 o Face Painting 11:00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m. FREE Family Portraits by Autumn Fue
 ntes 11:00 a.m. - 1:30 p.m. DJ Bianka from Cute Coffee 1:30 p.m. - 2:00 p.
 m. Performance by Ballet Folklorico Paquiyollotzin .fe-block-yui_3_17_2_1_
 1772665602507_5585 {mix-blend-mode: \; } SPRING BY THE RIVER PARTICIPANTS 
 .fe-block-yui_3_17_2_1_1773699012960_6951 {mix-blend-mode: \; } Huukuiko\,
  Inc. Mountain Star Handmade Technicolor Dino The Velvet Chapter Bookshop 
 .fe-block-yui_3_17_2_1_1773167649516_8044 {mix-blend-mode: \; } KNOW BEFOR
 E YOU GO! Getting Here Since parking is extremely limited—and we’re ob
 viously keen on green —we strongly recommend walking\, biking or public 
 transportation.&nbsp\; 👟 By Foot : The park entrance is at the intersec
 tion of Copeland and East D Streets\, in central Petaluma.&nbsp\; 🚲 By 
 Bike: Pedal over and lock up at the racks in front of the park entrance. 
 🚎 By Public Transportation: The park is a short\, ¼-mile walk from:&nb
 sp\; Petaluma SMART Train station at 200 Lakeville Street&nbsp\; Petaluma 
 Transit Routes 10 or 11—Copeland Street stop&nbsp\; And LumaGo will take
  you right to the park! What to Bring Your wallet—for lots of yummy item
 s and beautiful handmade goods! A partner\, a friend\, your grandmother\, 
 your kids! Did we mention the FREE portraits?&nbsp\; Sunscreen\, hats\, wa
 ter\, picnic blankets\, and comfortable shoes. (Mud alert if it rained the
  day before.) Fido! Dogs are always welcome\, as long as pup stays on leas
 h. A Few More Details Paths and parking will be very limited access while 
 we’re setting up that morning. We love birds at the park\, but please no
  early birds to the event. There are two accessible portable restrooms—o
 ne near the central gathering area and one near the David Yearsley River H
 eritage Center. The perimeter trail is off-road wheelchair and stroller ac
 cessible. It’s looking like a sunny day—note that shade is limited. EV
 ENT VOLUNTEERS We need volunteers for this all-hands-on-deck event! Respon
 sibilities include set-up and break-down\, greeting and familiarizing visi
 tors with the Petaluma River Park project\, and supporting some of our fam
 ily-friendly activities.&nbsp\; .fe-block-yui_3_17_2_1_1773699012960_6097 
 {mix-blend-mode: \; } Sign up for a volunteer shift #block-yui_3_17_2_1_17
